### Page 2

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 2 of 11

The selections made in this section affect how the Nutrient Analysis is performed on the Menus.
10. Enter an amount in the Choose column for each Category as needed
The amount entered represents the amount a student is allowed to have from each Category.
11. Enter an amount in the Projected Meal Count column for each Serving Group as needed
The amount will be a percentage if the Projected Servings Count as a Percentage checkbox is checked.
12. Click the Checkbox(es) in the OVS column for each Serving Group as needed

13. Click the SAVE button to create the Menu
The page refreshes and a success message
displays.
The Edit Menus page displays.

### Page 3

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 3 of 11

ADD MENU ITEMS TO THE MENU
Once the Menu has been created, additional buttons will appear below to add Menu Items. Items can be added using
the ADD MENU ITEMS or ADD MENU ITEMS FROM QUICK LIST buttons.
1. Click the ADD MENU ITEMS button
A page displays a list of Menu Items
available to add to the Menu.
2. Click the Checkbox(es) to select the desired Menu Item(s)
Filters are available below each column header to search for Menu Items.
The Checkbox(es) will illuminate purple for the selected Menu Item(s).

3. Click the ADD ITEM(S) button to add the
selected Menu Item(s) to the Menu
The page refreshes and a success message
displays.
The user is returned to the Edit Menus
page.

### Page 4

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 4 of 11

Once the Menu Items are added to the Menu, the user can do the following:
a. Click the X icon to remove Menu Items
b. Click the Info icon to view the Menu Item Information
This contains information such as the Recipe Name, Serving Size, etc.
c. Click the SERVE WITH button to indicate that multiple Menu Items can be served together
See the Serve with Other Menu Items section for more information.

4. Enter the Projected Serving counts for each Serving Group
If the Projected Servings Count as a Percentage checkbox is checked, a percentage is entered in the field with the
count displayed to the right.
5. Select the Serving Size for each selected Menu Item and Serving Group

6. Click the SAVE button to add the Menu
Items
A success message displays.

### Page 5

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 5 of 11

ADD MENU ITEMS FROM MENU ITEM QUICK LIST
The ADD MENU ITEMS FROM QUICK LIST button can add multiple Menu Items from a list in one quick process.
If users need to manage Quick Lists before adding them to the Menu, refer to the Menu Item Quick List Quick
Guide.
1. Click the ADD MENU ITEMS FROM QUICK
LIST button
The Menu Item Quick List slide deck
displays.
2. Click the arrow to expand the desired
Quick List
The user can edit the Quick List by clicking
the Edit icon.

The user can manage all Quick Lists by clicking
the GO TO QUICKLIST CONFIG button at the
bottom of the slide deck.
3. Click the Checkbox(es) to select the desired
Menu Item(s)
Click the header Checkbox to select all
Menu Items.
The Checkbox(es) will illuminate purple for
the selected Menu Item(s).
4. Verify or enter the Projected Serving
counts for each selected Menu Item

### Page 6

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
