5. Click the ADD TO MENU button to add the
selected Menu Item(s) to the Menu
The page refreshes and a success message
displays.
The user is returned to the Edit Menus
page.

The Menu Items are added to the Menu.

### Page 7

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 7 of 11

SERVE WITH OTHER MENU ITEMS
The SERVE WITH button indicates that multiple Menu Items can be served together. An example of how this feature is
useful is when side Items are served with an entrée.
1. Click the SERVE WITH button
The Menu Items to Serve With pop-up
window displays.

2. Click the Checkbox(es) to select the desired Item(s) to accompany this Item in serving
The Checkbox(es) will illuminate purple for the selected Item(s).
3. Click the ADD button to link the Item(s) for serving
The page refreshes and a success message displays.

### Page 8

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 8 of 11

The added Item displays under Serve With: for the Menu Item. This Item will still be listed separately under its
respective Menu Item Category as a Complementary Item of.

4. Click the SAVE button to retain changes
The page refreshes and a success message
displays.

### Page 9

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 9 of 11

VIEW MENU ANALYSIS
The Analysis feature verifies that all nutrient and meal contributions comply with the requirements defined by USDA.
Unsaved changes to the Menu will not be reflected on the Analysis page. Be sure to click the SAVE button before
reviewing the analysis.
1. Click the ANALYSIS button
The Menu Analysis slide deck displays.

2. Click the Show Only Required toggle switch on or off as needed
The nutrients and food components will display when enabled to reflect the USDA requirements.
The Menu Analysis slide deck displays the nutrient and meal contribution details. Notice the three color-coding keys
below the table. If any nutrients from ingredients in this Menu have Exceeded, are High / Fail, or are Low, the ACTUAL
value column will highlight the color corresponding to the warning.

### Page 10

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 10 of 11

VIEW THE MENU DAY NUTRIENT ANALYSIS REPORT
Users can generate the Menu Day Nutrient Analysis Report from the Menu Analysis slide deck.
On the Menu Analysis slide deck
1. Click the NUTRITION REPORT button to get
a detailed printable report for the nutrition
analysis
The Menu Day Nutrient Analysis Report
displays in another tab, showing the
nutrient analysis.

a. Select a Nutrition Option from the dropdown to view ALL, Expanded, or Simplified versions of the report
b. Click the Printer icon to export the report
c. View information such as the Menu, Result, Meal Pattern, Meal Type, Serving Group, and Site Group
Notice that the Result for this Menu will show the outcome of Pass or Fail.
d. View the Nutrient Summary
e. View the Food Component Summary

### Page 11

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Menu Planning
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 11 of 11

f. View each Menu Items nutrient information
Use the scroll bar at the bottom of the table to view additional columns.
